review_blob: On tap. Chocolate and caramel with some hop bitterness to balance the bready sweetness. Black malt dryness comes through with a hint of smoke and ginger. Excellent balance. Wonderful chocolate and roast aroma with a long rich finish. Wonderful.
Great example of this style. I picked up this bottle at my local bottle shop. A nice balance of the lactic acid with a hint of wheat sweetness to balance. Wonderful on a hot day.
A nice aroma of roast and dark chocolate. Medium to full mouthfeel with a dark chocolate bitterness supporting the roasted malt. Long roasty finish. Yummy!

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Honey aroma with almost a candy sweetness. Floral notes reminaniscent of hibiscus flowers. Like a nectar for adults.
low malt with a bit of a dry finish, lots of yeast in the bottle. tastes like US hops
Lager clean straw hay aroma. Dark gold with a low head. Grassy hops are in the forefront with a medium mouthfeel and a malty finish, not sweet. Very drinkable as a full bodied lager style.

Poured on draft. Low head & very cloudy almost opaque light gold. Low aroma of lemons/citrus and wheat. Not your typical wit. Medium bodied and a taste of yeast with a citrus finish. This example coul d use more carbonation but an interesting example of the style.

Pours dark and opaque with a slow to form tan head. Aromas of chocolate, heavy roast, caramel malt sweetness. Nice lacing on the glass as you drink it. Roasted bitterness is predominant and lingering into the finish. Malt sweetness and chocolate/caramel are present but the flavor ends with roast, not hop bitterness. A wonderful example of this style.

Low roasted malt aroma with some notes of vanilla & dark chocolate. Tall tan head that lingers with fine cascading bubbles that cling to the glass like a sheer curtain. The spicy notes of the Palo Santo wood come through, reminiscent of sandalwood or of incence, creating a playful balance between the roast, vanilla & chocolate. The long finish ends with a peppery or of a middle eastern spice. Quite yummy.

whoa, quite a flavor of sweetness & bitterness. Dark brown with ruby highlights and a medium tan head. rich flavor of raisins, toffee, burnt sugar and a dry roast bitterness that lingers into the finish. One to try especially on tap.
Fresh raspberries are the defining aroma & flavor of this beer. Like a mouthfull of fresh fruit. Wonderful Belgian lace from a frothy white head.

Mild chocolate & roast aroma. Full creamy tan head that stays through to the last sip. Dark chocolate is the dominant flavor with a long bittersweet finish. Full mouthfeel like a melting chocolate bar. Always a favorite.

Aroma of dark roasted chocolate with a low off-white head that barely lingered. Roasted grain with a distinct taste of dark cacao with a long slightly burnt finish. Full bodied, rich and savory. Yummy.
Rich aroma of coffee, chocolate & bourbon. A nice balance of all three flavors with some additional caramel and some lingering toffee sweetness. a nice example of a bourbon aged beer.
beer_name: Flying Dog Wild Dog Barrel-Aged Gonzo

review_blob: Grassy hops with some pils malt sweetness. Grassy hops dominate then fade into a firm malt backbone. Hops last long into the finish. Very refreshing an good with food.
Great chocolate & roast aroma with some dark fruit aromas. Medium mouthfeel, low chocolate bitterness with more hop than malt. Short bitter finish. Left wanting more malt!

On tap @ Sergios. Toasty, roasty, malty sweet aroma. Low carbonation, opaque dark brown with a low tan head. Oatmeal slickness/fullness on the palette, medium roast and bready flavors. Rich full mouthfeel. Would like to taste it again with more carbonation; but very good.

Tart, lactic nose with a slight aroma of brett. Pours hazy yellow with a tall white head that quickly falls. Low carbonation but lovely foam lacing on the glass as it falls. Tangy sourness followed by a full wheat malt palette that lingers into the finish. Low alcohol and very quaffable. Could use more carbonation and perhaps a bit more sourness.

Citrus with some low caramel notes. On tap @ Sergios. Dense copper color with a tall, fluffy off-white head that lingers leaving lace on the glass. Citrus hops dominate with the malty caramel, toffee backbone holding up the bitterness long into the finish.
beer_name: Flying Dog Double Dog Double Pale Ale

review_blob: On draft @ Sergios. Rich caramel with citrus notes. Deep copper color with aa small off-white head that faded quickly. Full-bodied with citrusy hoppy bitterness that overtakes the rich layers of caramel and toffee. No astringency from the wood aging; just a smooth, rich double IPA.
beer_name: Great Divide Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA

review_blob: On draft @ Flanigans. Slightly sweet Pils malt aroma, clean lager taste with a crisp finish. A nice clean lager with noble hop flavor.

Poured on tap with a tall, full white head. Aroma of banana & clove with malty, toasty notes. Smooth, medium bodied wheat malt flavor with a background of banana & clove with some slight caramel. Long smooth finish.

Bottle as gift. Malty, toasty, fruit-like (prune) aroma & pours amber with low carbonation and a low white head that dissapated quickly. Medium full body, rich malty flavors with melanoidins & sweetness from the malt. Low to no hop flavor, rich & smooth with some alcohol warmness. Long malty finish. A nice beer for a cold January evening.

Bottle from Keg Liquors, IN. Aroma of roasted malt and carmel and toffee, slight coffee. Pours dark brown with a tan head that lingers. Coffee, chocolate, smooth medium mouthfeel. Long finish of roast and coffee.

On tap at Flanigans Ale House. Malty, caramel aroma; no hops. Nice off-white head that lingered. Rich malt flavor with caramel and toffee notes; low to no hops. Balanced. Tasted like a scottish 70 shilling. An easy drinking pint. Didnt get any of the spices that were advertised in this sample.

Bottle @ Flanigans Ale house. No aroma, but waited since it was cold...then still hard to get any aroma. Low carbonation, medium to full mouthfeel. Bittersweet chocolate flavors with maple and some dark fruit. Long smooth finish. Easy to drink, more like a lower alcohol beer. A sipper with some complexity but not as much as I expected from these breweries. A nice beer overall.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Dogfish Head Life & Limb

review_blob: On tap @ Flanigan Ale House. Malty toasty aroma; medium bodied. Toasted & biscuit flavors, medium hop with some malt sweetness in the finish. A nice representation of an English IPA.
Bottle @ Flanigans Ale House. Strong citrus hop aroma with a bit of caramel. Medium bodied with malty citrus flavor, more like an American IPA. Nice beer.

Bottle from Keg Liquors, IN. Pours inky black brown with a full dark tan head with small bubbles that lingers. Aromas of dark fruit, chocolate, roast and some alcohol. Flavors of roast, dark bitter chocolate and some creaminess from the wheat malt. Long finish. Deceptively smooth for such a big beer. Excellent with an aged cheddar.

I had the Dogfish World Wide Stout on tap at Sergios World Beers. Yes, 18% is a sipper for sure. Roasty aromas with some dark fruit. Full mouthfeel with chocolate and layers of roasted malts and caramel sweetness that was balanced by the hops. Very smooth, you dont realize how much alcohol by the taste. Very good.

Bottle from Valu Mart. Tart Mortmencery cherry aroma dominates. Tall off-white head. Medium mouthfeel, and thd flavor is "cherry all the time". Like a cherry soda that happens to be a Belgian beer. Awesome.

Bottle, blend 2, 2009 from Keg Liquors, IN. Aroma of brett, some malt sweetness. Medium mouthfeel, brett is mild as is the malt. Low to no hop flavor. Low carbonation. A mild tasting belgian style ale with a bit of brett. The bottle mentions cacao & spices but I didnt get much from this bottle. But an easy drinking brew and a good introduction to my friends for artisian ales.

On tap @ Sergios World Beers. Aroma of grapefruit and caramel malt sweetness. Hop forward but balanced by the malt. Caramel malt with the hops linger into the finish. Full bodied beer and easy to drink.

On tap @ Sergios World Beers. Pours opaque black with a tall tan head. Roast aroma with some toasty notes in the aroma. Full-bodied mouthfeel, rich roasty, malty, chocolately flavors with an underlying sweetness. Long finish of all those flavors. One not to pass up.

On tap @ Sergios World Beers. Clove and other holiday spices eith a slight caramel malt aroma. Spice forward with a rich malty backbone of caramel and some toffee that last into the finish. Would like to try this beer again in a few months as the spices mellow. Well done.

12oz bottle. Pours dark gold with a tall off-white head. Citrus hop aroma with faint whiffs of toast and light caramel. Medium to full bodied, bitter flavor up front, then malt with some sweetness with a long grapefruit finish. A nice beer for the cold weather. Very drinkable.
Bottle was a gift. Pours a deep red with a full white head. Wow, what cherry aroma and a flavor to match. Tart Montmorency cherries dominate; it doesnt even taste like a beer. Awesome.
A gift shared with friends. Pours amber with a frothy white head that lingers. Carmelly, toffee, malty sweetness, no hops. Smooth medium mouthfeel. A nice easy to drink Belgian Special Ale.

Bottle from Keg Liquors, IN. Coffee, toffee, chocolate aromas. Opaque, black-brown pouring with a dk tan head with large bubbles that lingers. Very rich malty, coffee flavor, hops to balance with a long finish. Alcohol is evident but hidden by the richness of the malt bill. Smooth, full-bodied with a slickness from the oatmeal. A different, amazing coffee with no acidity bite. Lovely.

Bottle from Valu Mart "beer cave". Aroma of roast and chocolate. Poured inky black with a small dark tan head that dissapated quickly. Rich melanoidens with chocolate & roast, medium body and a long roasty finish. a wonderful black lager, American style.

Bottle from Keg Liquors, IN. Deep brown with ruby highlights. Tall tan head with fine bubbles, medium carbonation that fell quickly. Aroma of chocolate and toasted malts with a bit of caramel. Tastes of chocolate, roast, some sweetness like toffee; low to no hops; balanced toward sweetness. Very drinkable, could have another.

Bottle:  Blend 1, 2009. Full fluffy white head, very effervescent. Aromas of caramel, toast, brett sourness. Deep amber color with a lingering rocky white head that laces on the glass as you drink it. Dark sour fruit layered with spices and a bit of oak. Long finish. An excellent holiday sipper.

On draft @ Sergios World Beers. Tons of grapefruit dominate the aroma. Pours with a tall, lingering white head that laces on the glass as you drink it. malt sweetness comes through the hop bitterness and both last into a long finish. Great beer.
carmely, hoppy, spice aroma. This  keg has a maltier and more pronounced blend of spices than the previous keg draft I had last week. This keg would meld the flavors in another month but a nice beer.

Bottle, 1pt 9.4 fl oz batch 367/368. Sweet honey and barnyard brett with citrus fruit. Tall rocky white head that lingers and leaves lacing on the glass. Sweet malt, lemony citrus and bitter brett flavor that last into the long finish.
